<section class="guideSection">
  <h2>Why Mini Greenhouse Covers Need Repair Kits</h2>

  <p>
    These covers are often exposed to wind, sun, and frequent handling. Zippers, seams, and corners tend to wear first, especially in changing weather conditions.
  </p>

  <p>
    Because the material is thinner, damage spreads faster if left untreated.
  </p>

  <p>
    Quick repairs prevent larger failures.
  </p>
</section>

<section class="guideSection">
  <h2>Essential Items in a Good Repair Kit</h2>

  <h3>UV-Resistant Patch Tape</h3>
  <p>
    The most important component for sealing tears and reinforcing weak areas.
  </p>

  <h3>Reinforcement Patches</h3>
  <p>
    Extra material for larger or high-stress repairs.
  </p>

  <h3>Cleaning Supplies</h3>
  <p>
    Ensures proper adhesion by removing dirt and moisture.
  </p>

  <h3>Cutting Tools</h3>
  <p>
    Allows clean, precise application of patches and tape.
  </p>
</section>

