<section class="guideSection">
  <h2>How to Repair Mini Greenhouse Covers</h2>

  <ol class="plainList">
    <li>Clean and dry the damaged area.</li>
    <li>Align the material if torn.</li>
    <li>Apply patch tape smoothly.</li>
    <li>Add reinforcement for larger tears.</li>
    <li>Press firmly to secure adhesion.</li>
  </ol>

  <p>
    Careful application makes repairs last longer.
  </p>
</section>

<section class="guideSection">
  <h2>Where Most Repairs Fail</h2>

  <h3>Poor Surface Preparation</h3>
  <p>
    Dirt and moisture reduce adhesion.
  </p>

  <h3>Using Non-UV Materials</h3>
  <p>
    Sun exposure breaks down standard tape quickly.
  </p>

  <h3>Not Reinforcing Stress Points</h3>
  <p>
    High-use areas need extra support.
  </p>

  <h3>Waiting Too Long</h3>
  <p>
    Small tears expand rapidly under stress.
  </p>
</section>

<section class="guideSection">
  <h2>When to Repair vs Replace</h2>

  <p>
    Repairs work best when damage is limited. If the cover is extensively worn or brittle, replacement may be more effective.
  </p>

  <p>
    Regular maintenance extends the lifespan significantly.
  </p>
</section>

